      "content": "Yes, there are a few more things you can try before calling your ISP. First, log into your router’s admin interface (usually via a browser at 192.168.0.1 or 192.168.1.1) and check the status page for any error messages or a “connected” indicator. If the router is a wireless router, try temporarily disabling and re-enabling the wireless radio to refresh the connection. Also, double-check the WAN or “Internet” port on the router to ensure it’s actually receiving a signal from your modem. If everything looks good in the settings and the red light persists, it might be a hardware issue or a line problem, so you may need to call the ISP after these steps.",
